book.part:
Overview
gives you an overview of GStreamer design goals.
rapidly covers the basics of GStreamer programming.
In we will move on to the examples. Since GStreamer uses GLib 2.0, the reader is assumed to understand the basics of the GObject object model.
For a gentle introduction to this system, you may wish to read the GTK+ Tutorial or Eric Harlow's book Developing Linux Applications with GTK+ and GDK.
&INTRO;
&MOTIVATION;
&GOALS;

Basic concepts



        We will first describe the basics of
        GStreamer programming by introducing the
        different objects needed to create a media pipeline.



        We will use a visual representation of these objects so that we can
	visualize the more complex pipelines you will learn to build later on.




